<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="h-full">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8"/>
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"/>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
    <title>Schtroumpsify Â· Phoenix Framework</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="<%= Routes.static_path(@conn, "/css/app.css") %>"/>
    <link href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lato&subset=latin,latin-ext' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-blue-100 text-gray-800 font-body flex flex-col h-full">

    <main role="main" class="p-5 flex-grow">
      <p class="alert alert-info" role="alert"><%= get_flash(@conn, :info) %></p>
      <p class="alert alert-danger" role="alert"><%= get_flash(@conn, :error) %></p>
      <%= render @view_module, @view_template, assigns %>
    </main>

    <footer class="bg-blue-500 text-sm text-blue-100">
		<div class="p-5 flex flex-col md:flex-row shadow-inner justify-center">
			<div class="lg:w-1/3 p-5 md:border-r border-blue-700">
				<div class="uppercase font-semibold tracking-wider mb-3 text-blue-200">What is this?</div>
				<div>
					<p class="mb-3">
						Would it be possible to make <a href="https://twitter.com/lemondefr">all tweets from Le Monde</a>, one of the main french newspapers, accessible to
						Smurfs ?
					</p>
					<p>
						That question deserved an answer so here is an experiment of translating french tweets to
						french smurf language, or <span class="italic">langue schtroumpf</span>, realtime and giving Smurfs
						an access to the world through <a href="https://twitter.com/leschtroumpffr">a dedicated twitter account</a>.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="md:w-1/3 p-5 md:border-l border-blue-400">
				<div class="uppercase font-semibold tracking-wider mb-5 text-blue-200">How does it work?</div>
				<div>
					<p class="mb-3">
						We subscribed to tweets from Le Monde and used the <a href="https://www.rocq.inria.fr/alpage-wiki/tiki-index.php?page=alpc&bl=y">Alpage toolchain</a>,
						developed by the INRIA, to parse the incoming tweets in order to obtain a syntactical analysis of the tweet content.
					</p>
					<p class="mb-3">
					Then we created a new tweet based on the type of words contained in the tweet and a
					dictionary of possible modification
					</p>
					<p class="mb-3">
					... and tweeted it!
					</p>
					<p>
					Feel free to dig in <a href="">the source code on Github</a>.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="flex justify-center flex-row pb-4">
			<div>Made by <a href="https://twitter.com/selrahcd">@Selrahcd</a></div>
		</div>
	</footer>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/socket.io/2.2.0/socket.io.slim.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="<%= Routes.static_path(@conn, "/js/app.js") %>"></script>
  </body>
</html>
